24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fa832ffa4e20c9aa05ac272214d43196?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dvasya%26avatarId%3D10408%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Vasiliy Kochergin","active":false,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"updated":"2015-05-08T17:00:43.152-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/10201","id":"10201","name":"AWS Compatibility"},{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/11500","id":"11500","name":"ELB","description":"Load Balancing"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"*Assessment*\r\n\r\nWhen stickiness session is configured for Eucalyptus ELB, the 'Cache-control' field in the response header is set to 'private'.  Per [RFC 2068|https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2068.txt], if 'private' is defined, it means the following:\r\n{quote}\r\nIndicates that all or part of the response message is intended for a\r\n  single user and MUST NOT be cached by a shared cache. This allows an\r\n  origin server to state that the specified parts of the response are\r\n  intended for only one user and are not a valid response for requests\r\n  by other users. A private (non-shared) cache may cache the response.\r\n{quote}\r\nBased upon [RFC 2616|https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2616.txt] under the section '14.9 Cache-Control', the cache-response-directive should be set to 'no-cache':\r\n{code}\r\n...\r\ncache-response-directive =\r\n           \"public\"                               ; Section 14.9.1\r\n         | \"private\" [ \"=\" <\"> 1#field-name <\"> ] ; Section 14.9.1\r\n         | \"no-cache\" [ \"=\" <\"> 1#field-name <\"> ]; Section 14.9.1\r\n         | \"no-store\"                             ; Section 14.9.2\r\n         | \"no-transform\"                         ; Section 14.9.5\r\n         | \"must-revalidate\"                      ; Section 14.9.4\r\n         | \"proxy-revalidate\"                     ; Section 14.9.4\r\n         | \"max-age\" \"=\" delta-seconds            ; Section 14.9.3\r\n         | \"s-maxage\" \"=\" delta-seconds           ; Section 14.9.3\r\n         | cache-extension                        ; Section 14.9.6\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n*Details*\r\n\r\nHere is a comparison of the 'Cache-control' directive between AWS and Eucalyptus ELB (both set up in the same manner):\r\n\r\n_Eucalyptus_\r\n{code}\r\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nServer: nginx/1.6.1 (Ubuntu)\r\nDate: Thu, 11 Sep 2014 01:21:10 GMT\r\nContent-Type: text/html\r\nContent-Length: 612\r\nLast-Modified: Tue, 05 Aug 2014 11:18:35 GMT\r\nETag: \"53e0bd8b-264\"\r\nAccept-Ranges: bytes\r\nSet-Cookie: AWSELB=MTAuMTA0LjYuMjMx|VBD5C|VBD5C; path=/\r\nCache-control: private\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n_AWS_\r\n{code}\r\nHTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\nAccept-Ranges: bytes\r\nCache-control: no-cache=\"set-cookie\"\r\nContent-length: 612\r\nContent-Type: text/html\r\nDate: Thu, 11 Sep 2014 16:02:00 GMT\r\nETag: \"5315bd25-264\"\r\nLast-Modified: Tue, 04 Mar 2014 11:46:45 GMT\r\nServer: nginx/1.4.6 (Ubuntu)\r\nSet-Cookie: AWSELB=31E1EBB9044FB36446CA398365E75F835BCFC584CE24665FFC3D06526BF80E4A5D94F71EF06D0A16FE2C3A2DC14B9B0AFC0B07AFDB7CC78414FDB89ABAA0D8C8F77EE9181A;PATH=/;MAX-AGE=30\r\nConnection: keep-alive\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThe key difference is that on AWS, the 'Cache-control' is set to {{no-cache=\"set-cookie\"}}, while the 'Cache-control' set on the Eucalyptus ELB is set to {{Cache-control: private}}.  The AWS response follows [RFC 2109|https://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc2109.txt], section 4.5  'Caching Proxy Role':\r\n{quote}\r\nCache the Set-Cookie subject to the control of the usual header,\r\n     Cache-control: no-cache=\"set-cookie\".  (The Set-Cookie header\r\n     should usually not be cached.)\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\n*Steps*\r\n\r\n# Set up a Eucalyptus 4.0.1 cloud with Eucalytpus DNS, Cloudformation and Load Balancer enabled\r\n# Bundle, upload and register an [Ubuntu Cloud Image (Trusty 14.04)|http://cloud-images.ubuntu.com/trusty/current/trusty-server-cloudimg-amd64-disk1.img] as an instance store-backed HVM EMI\r\n# (Optional) Set up HTTPS/SSL for ELB\r\n** [Uploading SSL Certificates for Elastic Load Balancing|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#user-guide/elb_examples_ssl_certificates.html]\r\n** [Creating a Basic Elastic Load Balancing Configuration|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#user-guide/elb_examples_basic_config.html]\r\n# Create an [Sticky Session policy (for example - Cookie Stickiness Policy)|https://www.eucalyptus.com/docs/eucalyptus/4.0.1/index.html#user-guide/elb_examples_sticky_sessions.html] and associate it with the LB port\r\n# Launch 2 instances using the Ubuntu image, and passing the cloud-init.config below to install Nginx:\r\n{code}\r\n$ cat nginx-cloudinit.config\r\n#cloud-config\r\napt_update: true\r\napt_upgrade: true\r\ndisable_root: true\r\npackages:\r\n - less\r\nruncmd:\r\n - [ sh, -xc, \"META_HOSTNAME=`curl -s http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/local-hostname`; META_IP=`curl -s http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/local-ipv4`; echo ${META_IP}   ${META_HOSTNAME} >> /etc/hosts\" ]\r\n - [ sh, -xc, \"META_HOSTNAME=`curl -s http://169.254.169.254/latest/meta-data/local-hostname`; hostname ${META_HOSTNAME}; sysctl -w kernel.hostname=${META_HOSTNAME}\" ]\r\n - [ apt-get, install, -y, --force-yes, dnsutils ]\r\n - [ apt-get, install, -y, --force-yes, bind9utils ]\r\n - [ apt-get, install, -y, --force-yes, mlocate ]\r\n - [ apt-get, install, -y, --force-yes, nginx ]\r\n{code}\r\n# Make sure port 80 is open in the security group associated with the instances - for 0.0.0.0/0\r\n# register the instances with the ELB\r\n# Run the 'curl' test in another terminal. Use the ELB DNS name in the test.  For example (_NOTE: if HTTPS/SSL is enabled, use the -k option with the curl command_):\r\n{code}\r\n# curl -I <ELB DNS name>\r\n{code}\r\n# Observe the output\r\n\r\n","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/user?username=spark","name":"spark","key":"spark","accountId":"557058:2ed923b8-7172-41f0-a425-8796bd9a62f9","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=48&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3FownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","24x24":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=24&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dsmall%26ownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","16x16":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=16&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dxsmall%26ownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue","32x32":"https://avatar-cdn.atlassian.com/fec440044f6e652174838d59d9233f29?s=32&d=https%3A%2F%2Feucalyptus.atlassian.net%2Fsecure%2Fuseravatar%3Fsize%3Dmedium%26ownerId%3Dspark%26avatarId%3D10900%26noRedirect%3Dtrue"},"displayName":"Sang-Min Park","active":false,"timeZone":"America/Los_Angeles"},"time